{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"This tutorial shows how to use GLib with Swift.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is particularly useful if you want to interact","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with libraries written in C or other languages that use GLib.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Tutorial"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Using GLib with Swift","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-GLib","text":"What is GLib?"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/glib\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"general-purpose software library that provides a set of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"useful data types, string utilities, filesystem abstractions,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a mainloop abstraction, and similar tools for developing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"libraries and applications in different programming languages.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GLIb is mainly used for creating and interacting with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"low-level data structures and supports features such as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"event-driven programming, memory management, and data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type management.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GLib is part of the GNOME project, but works with different"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Operating Systems, including Linux and macOS."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Swift-Bindings","text":"Swift Bindings","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Swift language bindings have been generated using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".gir"},{"type":"text","text":" files from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/gi.readthedocs.io\/en\/latest\/"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowing a more “swifty” use of the library than using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"through the low-level C interface.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Particularly the collection interfaces, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/rhx.github.io\/SwiftGLib\/GLib\/documentation\/glib\/typedslist"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/rhx.github.io\/SwiftGLib\/GLib\/documentation\/glib\/typedlist"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allow to use templated Swift data types rather than raw"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pointers.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Prerequisites","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To get the most out of this tutorial, you should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"generally familiar with Linux, macOS, or other UNIX-like"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"environments and know how to use a command-line shell"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.gnu.org\/software\/bash\/"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.zsh.org\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You will need a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/getting-started\/cli-swiftpm\/"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/support\/xcode\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if you are running macOS, or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly for your Operating System."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You also need to install the GLib development libraries","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for your system.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Installing-GLib-on-Linux","text":"Installing GLib on Linux"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most modern Linux distributions come with the GLib runtime","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preinstalled, but you will need to install the headers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"necessary for development."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This can be done using the package manager for your system.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, on Ubuntu or other Debian-based systems,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"you can use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wiki.debian.org\/Apt","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"manager using the following commands:"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["sudo apt update","sudo apt install libglib2.0-dev glib-networking gobject-introspection libgirepository1.0-dev libxml2-dev jq"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Depending on your Linux distributions, the names of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"packages and package management tools will vary."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You should be able to find this in the documentation for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"your Linux distribution.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some more examples can also be found in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/rhx\/SwiftGLib\/blob\/main\/README.md","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"tip","type":"aside"},{"level":3,"text":"Installing GLib on macOS","type":"heading","anchor":"Installing-GLib-on-macOS"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For macOS, there are multiple package management tools"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that you can use."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/brew.sh\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is one example."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After you have installed HomeBrew, you can install"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GLib using:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["brew update","brew install glib glib-networking gobject-introspection pkg-config jq"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Compiling-SwiftGLib-programs","type":"heading","text":"Compiling SwiftGLib programs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The easiest way to compile programs and libraries using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SwiftGLib is through projects using the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/swift.org\/package-manager\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Here is an example for a simple program that uses a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/rhx.github.io\/SwiftGLib\/GLib\/documentation\/glib\/typedlist","overridingTitle":"type list","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"type list"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"First, create a directory (folder) for your project, then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create the project inside the folder:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["mkdir swift-glist","cd swift-glist","swift package init --type=executable"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will create a simple “Hello World” executable that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you can test using "},{"code":"swift run","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" – the program will run","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and print “Hello world”.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you look at the files generated by ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift package init","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"you will find a file named ","type":"text"},{"code":"Package.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that represents"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the project and its compilation targets."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Overall, if you run"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["find * -type f"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"you should see two files, the aforementioned ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and a "},{"code":"main.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sources\/swift-glist"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["Package.swift","Sources\/swift-glist\/main.swift"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some versions of the Swift Package manager create"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a flat structure when using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift package init"},{"type":"text","text":" that puts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main.swift"},{"text":" directly in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sources"},{"text":" folder.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This will cause the Swift compiler to exit with an error if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you try to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift run"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Warning","type":"aside","style":"warning"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Such a faulty structure that places your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main.swift"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directly in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sources","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" folder would look like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Package.swift","Sources\/main.swift"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this case, your program won’t compile or run.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"To fix this, you need to move the ","type":"text"},{"code":"main.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-glist"},{"type":"text","text":" subfolder:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["mkdir Sources\/swift-glist","mv Sources\/main.swift Sources\/swift-glist\/"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now you should be able to build your project.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let us now change the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" file so that it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reads:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"Swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ swift-tools-version: 5.7","","import PackageDescription","","let package = Package(","    name: \"swift-glist\",","    dependencies: [","        .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/rhx\/gir2swift.git\", branch: \"main\"),","        .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/rhx\/SwiftGLib.git\", branch: \"main\"),","    ],","    targets: [","        .executableTarget(","            name: \"swift-glist\",","            dependencies: [","                .product(name: \"GLib\", package: \"SwiftGLib\"),","            ]","        ),","    ]",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will add the relevant dependencies for SwiftGLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the project.  We can now change the code in our","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sources\/swift-glist\/main.swift"},{"text":" so that it reads:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["import GLib","","let list: TypedList = [\"Hello\", \"world\"]","","print(list.length())  \/\/ Prints: 2","","list.forEach { element in","    print(element)    \/\/ Prints: \"hello\" and \"world\"","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"Swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compile and run the code using:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["swift run"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After some compiler output (and potentially"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some warnings that you can ignore), you should get the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"following output:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["2","Hello","world"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/tutorial"]}],"references":{"https://gi.readthedocs.io/en/latest/":{"url":"https:\/\/gi.readthedocs.io\/en\/latest\/","